<p><b>Steven M. Bellovin</b> is a researcher on <a href="/wiki/Computer_networking" title="Computer networking" class="mw-redirect">computer networking</a> and <a href="/wiki/Computer_security" title="Computer security">security</a>. He is currently a Professor in the Computer Science department at <a href="/wiki/Columbia_University" title="Columbia University">Columbia University</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> having previously been a Fellow at <a href="/wiki/AT%26T_Labs" title="AT&amp;T Labs">AT&amp;T Labs</a> Research in <a href="/wiki/Florham_Park" title="Florham Park" class="mw-redirect">Florham Park</a>, <a href="/wiki/New_Jersey" title="New Jersey">New Jersey</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>In September 2012, Bellovin was appointed Chief Technologist for the United States <a href="/wiki/Federal_Trade_Commission" title="Federal Trade Commission">Federal Trade Commission</a>, replacing <a href="/wiki/Edward_Felten" title="Edward Felten">Edward W. Felten</a>, who returned to <a href="/wiki/Princeton_University" title="Princeton University">Princeton University</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-FTC_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FTC-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
